OL,7,FThe ASA said the use of different skin
OL,8,Fcolours was a means of portraying a
OL,9,F"before and after" of the product's
OL,10,Fuse, which created a juxtaposition of
OL,11,Fblack skin shown as itchy, dry and
OL,12,Fcracked in the "before" scenes, and
OL,13,Fwhite skin shown as smoother skin in
OL,14,Fthe "after" scenes.
