OL,7,FThe ASA added: "Although we understood
OL,8,Fthat this message was not the one
OL,9,Fintended and might appear coincidental
OL,10,For pass unnoticed by some viewers, we
OL,11,Fconsidered that the ad was likely to
OL,12,Freinforce the negative and offensive
OL,13,Fracial stereotype that black skin was
OL,14,Fproblematic and that white skin was
OL,15,Fsuperior.
OL,17,F"We concluded that the ad included a
OL,18,Fracial stereotype and was therefore
OL,19,Flikely to cause serious offence."
